    "goal_understanding": "The goal of the game is to navigate a grid-based environment, adjusting your piece's shape, color, and rotation using modifier tiles to match the requirements of goal cells, then step onto those goal cells to complete them. You must complete all goal cells in each level while managing stamina and lives to advance through all levels and win the game.",
    "mechanics_understanding": "Each move costs 1 stamina. If stamina reaches 0, you lose a life and stamina resets to its maximum. Losing all lives results in game over. Walls block movement, and you must avoid moving into blocked directions. Modifier tiles change your piece's attributes: shape changers cycle the shape (0\u20135), color changers cycle through orange, blue, green, red, and rotation changers rotate 90\u00b0 clockwise. A goal cell becomes activated only when your piece's shape, color, and rotation all match the goal's requirements. Once activated, stepping onto the goal cell completes it. You can only complete a goal by actually moving onto its cell. The coordinate system uses x and y, with MOVE_NORTH decreasing y, MOVE_SOUTH increasing y, MOVE_EAST increasing x, and MOVE_WEST decreasing x."
